The built-in data types in TypeScript include:

* boolean
* number
* string
* null
* undefined
* any
* void
* never
* object
* array
* tuple

For example, here's how you can declare variables using some of these data types:
```typescript
let isDone: boolean = false;
let myNumber: number = 42;
let myString: string = "Hello, world!";
let myNull: null = null;
let myUndefined: undefined = undefined;
let myAny: any = "This can be any data type";
let myVoid: void = undefined;
let myNever: never = (() => { throw new Error("This function never returns!"); })();
let myObject: object = {name: "Alice", age: 30};
let myArray: number[] = [1, 2, 3];
let myTuple: [string, number] = ["foo", 42];
```
